    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-22T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-22T15:00:00-05:00" n="803"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d803">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/6–2254: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-22T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 22, 1954—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 501. Rptd information Paris 483, Saigon
                    196. Paris eyes only Ambassador, Saigon eyes only. Department limit
                    distribution. <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> told me this
                    afternoon that <persName corresp="#p_CEL1">Chou En-lai</persName>–<persName
                        corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes-France</persName> meeting had been arranged for
                    tomorrow at Bern “under cover” courtesy visit by <persName corresp="#p_MFP1"
                        >Mendes-France</persName> to Bern. However, announcement will probably be
                    made this evening that he will also see <persName corresp="#p_CEL1">Chou
                        En-lai</persName>.</p>
                <p>There was opportunity only to obtain brief account <persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                        >Chauvel</persName>’s meeting with <persName corresp="#p_PVD1"
                        >Dong</persName> today. <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> said
                    that <persName corresp="#p_PVD1">Dong</persName> stated agreement on Vietnam
                    could be reached within ten days in “underground military talks”, and <persName
                        corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> added it would take another five days
                    “to sell” the Vietnamese.<note n="1" xml:id="d803fn1">In telegram <gloss
                            target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 506, June 23, the U.S. Delegation
                        instructed the Department of State to “Correct second sentence paragraph
                            <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 501 to read as follows:
                            ‘<persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> said that <persName
                            corresp="#p_PVD1">Dong</persName> stated agreement on Vietnam could be
                        reached within ten days in “underground military talks” (which <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> expects to be resumed Thursday) and
                            <persName corresp="#p_PVD1">Dong</persName> expected it would take
                        another five days “to sell” the Vietnamese.’” (396.1 GE/6–2354)</note> I
                    asked him what this portended as far as Hanoi-Haiphong perimeter was concerned
                    and received vague answer to effect was making attempt to hold on to that area
                    “for time being” on grounds of military necessity and that with passage of time
                    lots of things could happen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
